climbs.name: What Up?
climbs.fa: Kelly Cordner, Jonathen Hartnett & Randy Jacobs 4/97

content.description:
This is currently the right-most route at the Warm Up Wall, and is located about 15' right of

Babushka

.

Climb a vertical face past edges with a distinct crux between the last two bolts - it's a little on the pumpy side if you read the moves wrong.

climbs.name: Welcome to the Gorge
climbs.fa: Scott Ayers, Eden Masters, Elizabeth Gorrin, 1992.

content.description:
This route is on the lower left side of the wall, as you approach the cliff.

9 bolts lead up the center of the face.

Tricky mantle moves lead to somewhat easier climbing.

This variation combines the best parts of the two climbs (as well as avoiding the awkward parts of both), for a really fun route mix-up! Bring 2 long/extra-long slings to reduce rope drag at the transition.

Climb the first section of "Wall Flower", clipping the first 5 bolts. Clip the 5th bolt with a long sling, then traverse left and up 10 feet on easy ground to gain the 6th bolt of "Welcome to the Gorge". Clip another long sling on this and continue up "Welcome to the Gorge" to the anchors.

Another option is to clip the "Welcome to the Gorge" anchors with a (longish) draw, then continue up past one more bolt to the anchors of "Sweet and Sour" (11 bolts total).
content.protection:
9 bolts, Mussy Hooks; to "Sweet and Sour" anchors: 11 bolts, Mussy Hooks.

Lower off
content.location: Start in the steep dihedral to the right of "Welcome to the Gorge"

content.description:
A nice route starting out in a short crack, followed by face climbing up to a gentle bulge. Probably the most densely bolted route on the warmup wall.

climbs.name: Clip Jr.
climbs.fa: Kelly Cordner, Brian Phillips, Scott Ayers, 4/1997.

content.description:
This climbs a pillar, on the right side of the lower left side of the wall, then up an arete.

Some tricky moves are encountered just before the anchors.

This is to the right of "Welcome to the Gorge".
near vertical with mostly buckets after the shallow dihedral start. Crux is above bolt 6.
Starts at the corner on the left side of the wall and then continues straight up the face when the ridge veers off to the left. Fairly big holds with a little quirkiness near the top.
